# Docker build-context excludes for the pi-runtime image.
#
# IMPORTANT: Docker only reads the .dockerignore at the BUILD CONTEXT ROOT.
# packages/runtime/Dockerfile is built with the MONOREPO ROOT as context
# (`-f packages/runtime/Dockerfile .`) because of the `file:../runtime-client`
# dep, so this file is effective only if the context root is packages/runtime.
# It is kept here next to the Dockerfile, scoped to that subtree, as a
# belt-and-suspenders guard and to document the intended ignores. The lead
# should mirror these patterns into a repo-root .dockerignore (see report).
#
# The Dockerfile's COPYs are already narrow (package.json, bun.lock, src,
# engine-client/{package.json,src}); these patterns shrink the context tar and
# stop stray dev artifacts from sneaking into a layer.

# Installed deps — reinstalled in-image via `bun install --frozen-lockfile`.
node_modules/

# VCS + OS noise.
.git/
.gitignore
.DS_Store

# Logs and local runtime data (HOUSTON_DATA_DIR / dataDir output).
*.log
data/

# Tests never run inside the image.
**/*.test.ts

# De-risk spikes are not part of the shipped engine.
spike/

# Docs / markdown add weight, never executed.
*.md
docs/

# The image runs source directly via Bun; no prebuilt dist is needed or wanted.
dist/
